events.name: Pinch, Graphs, Aquarian, True Nature
events.description: Pinch brings an otherworldly mix of deep, dark & broken-beat techno rhythms, seismic UK-dubstep, grime, dancehall, and future-dub. He brings along Graphs, Aquarian, and True Nature for a dubby night of exquisite musical selections.

events.name: Synthicide
events.description: Synth-driven sets from Jeffo!, DJ O, mac, Fade Kainer, and Andi. Event thrown in conjunction with the Nowhere to Run Festival, celebrating the post-punk community through the years and around the world in NYC.

events.name: Femmequerade Ball
events.description: This party is taking over Good Room and turning it into a specifically queer/femme-positive space! It’s co-hosted by Brujas, the Bronx-based all-woman skater crew (recently profiled in the NY Times), as well as an inclusive electronic music collective known as Sister, and a satirical “art-bro” duo called Hot Schmucks. Door tickets are $18 for cis straight white men and $15 for everyone else.

events.name: Confused House
events.description: A pioneer of the NYC techno scene known for crossing between techno and industrial, Adam X promises to deliver a hard-hitting set punctuated by ambient and minimal sounds that somehow fall perfectly into place. He's joined by Antenes, one of our local favorites known for delivering eclectic techno sets that drift into experimental and psychedelic realms.
